full_text: 127 Form I-423 UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION SERVICE (Rev. 5-5-53) REQUEST FOR VERIFICATION OF ARRIVAL 31 TAILL Cleveland, Ohio Office of origin. A-10394732 HC N-600 File number. June 29, 1956 JUL 2 MAIL JUL RECORDS 1956 UNIT 2 Alien number. Date. TO: District Director, New York, N. Y. It is requested that a search be made for a record of the entry into the United States of the person named below. If arrival is verified, please indicate by the following action: NT Forward 1 copies of Form I-404 or I-404-A. Check the data below. Indicate discrepancies, if any. Moses Milstein (1) Present name. Moses Milstein (2) Name used at time of entry. New York, N. Y. (3) Port of entry. March or April, 1938 (4) Date of entry. unknown (5) Name of vessel or other means of conveyance. Luck, Poland (6) Place of birth. (City or town) (State) (Country) unknown (7) Age at time of entry. none (8) Names of accompanying passen- gers. Sarah Milstein, 2803 Avondale Rd., (9) Name and address of person to Cleveland Hts., Ohio whom destined. Palestine (Israel) (10) Port of embarkation. REMARKS This information is desired in order to locate his visa and in turn to obtain the visa petition number filed in his behalf by his wife, Sarah. No further information appears to be available. John Acting District Director (Name of official) pilman (Title) REPORT OF SEARCH Port of entry. Remarks Date. Arrival verified as requested. CIV. NO. CLASS PLACE AND DATE OF ISSUE R.P.NO. CHARGE TO QUOTA HEAD TAX STATUS Unable to verify on basis of above information. Ax25-63-13216 B The following records have been searched: Card index. Index books. Manifests.
